[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman in court over OAP Mary Logie's death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 40-year-old woman has appeared in court charged with the murder of a Fife grandmother.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Sandra Weir is accused of killing her neighbour 82-year-old Mary Logie. Both women lived in Green Gates in Leven.
The pensioner was found dead in her home on 5 January.
Ms Weir made no plea or declaration during a hearing at Kirkcaldy Sheriff Court.
